1
00:00:35,875 --> 00:00:38,791
♪

2
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:46,708
[bell ringing]

3
00:00:51,291 --> 00:00:52,500
[PRISONER 1]
We're under attack!

4
00:00:52,583 --> 00:00:53,916
[PRISONER 2]
It's the Seventh Division!

5
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,791
[PRISONER 3]
We're all gonna get killed!

6
00:00:55,875 --> 00:00:57,500
Open the doors!

7
00:00:59,125 --> 00:01:01,458
This is great.
What the hell do we do?

8
00:01:01,541 --> 00:01:03,250
We run, Shiraishi.

9
00:01:03,333 --> 00:01:06,125
How about you think of a way
to get us out, Escape King?

10
00:01:06,208 --> 00:01:07,916
[grunting]

11
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:15,500
Hold it right there.

12
00:01:15,583 --> 00:01:17,625
Afraid you're not
going anywhere just yet.

13
00:01:17,708 --> 00:01:20,000
♪

14
00:02:51,625 --> 00:02:53,041
[bell ringing]

15
00:02:53,125 --> 00:02:54,625
[TANIGAKI]
Let me get this straight.

16
00:02:54,708 --> 00:02:57,666
This whole time, you've been
with Lieutenant Tsurumi?

17
00:02:57,750 --> 00:02:58,833
-Why?
-[ringing continues]

18
00:02:58,916 --> 00:02:59,875
[INKARMAT]
You hear that?

19
00:02:59,958 --> 00:03:02,125
Sugimoto's group has failed.

20
00:03:02,208 --> 00:03:03,333
Know what that means?

21
00:03:03,416 --> 00:03:04,791
Now Tsurumi's the only one

22
00:03:04,875 --> 00:03:07,125
who can get
Nopperabo and Asirpa out.

23
00:03:07,208 --> 00:03:09,625
The trap has been sprung.

24
00:03:09,708 --> 00:03:11,250
I don't understand.

25
00:03:11,333 --> 00:03:13,791
The Seventh would get
all that Ainu gold.

26
00:03:13,875 --> 00:03:15,625
Now you're okay with that?

27
00:03:15,708 --> 00:03:18,208
[INKARMAT]
Let's be honest with each other.

28
00:03:18,291 --> 00:03:20,708
It doesn't matter to me
who gets that gold,

29
00:03:20,791 --> 00:03:23,333
and I suspect it doesn't matter
much to you, either.

30
00:03:25,458 --> 00:03:27,958
[TANIGAKI]
Women are terrifying creatures.

31
00:03:28,041 --> 00:03:29,666
[INUDOU]
You know what to do.

32
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:32,083
Get to your positions
and remember your training.

33
00:03:32,166 --> 00:03:34,416
Put the Maxim guns
on both sides of the gate.

34
00:03:35,458 --> 00:03:36,916
Concentrate your fire
on the entrance

35
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,083
when they break through,

36
00:03:38,166 --> 00:03:40,208
and be relentless.

37
00:03:40,291 --> 00:03:42,541
We're about to rip
these guys apart.

38
00:03:42,625 --> 00:03:45,458
This is gonna save us
a fortune on pig food.

39
00:03:45,541 --> 00:03:47,958
♪

40
00:03:48,041 --> 00:03:49,166
[gasps]

41
00:03:49,250 --> 00:03:50,458
Into the tunnel.

42
00:03:50,541 --> 00:03:51,541
Hurry!

43
00:03:53,708 --> 00:03:55,958
♪

44
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:11,583
[SOLDIER]
Fire!

45
00:04:21,375 --> 00:04:22,625
[screams]

46
00:04:28,083 --> 00:04:29,625
-[explosion]
-[TONI groaning]

47
00:04:35,541 --> 00:04:37,250
I thought you wanted
to see your father.

48
00:04:40,750 --> 00:04:42,000
Hmm.

49
00:04:46,458 --> 00:04:48,708
Damn, that can't be good.

50
00:04:48,791 --> 00:04:49,916
Time to go.

51
00:04:53,458 --> 00:04:55,625
That's the wall
facing the river.

52
00:04:55,708 --> 00:04:57,166
They've outsmarted us!

53
00:04:57,250 --> 00:05:00,458
♪

54
00:05:06,458 --> 00:05:07,875
[HAJIME]
Excuse me, Lieutenant.

55
00:05:07,958 --> 00:05:10,000
If I may ask, what do you intend

56
00:05:10,083 --> 00:05:12,500
to tell Central Command
about this?

57
00:05:12,583 --> 00:05:14,625
Locusts, I think.

58
00:05:14,708 --> 00:05:16,458
Locusts?

59
00:05:16,541 --> 00:05:18,083
[TSURUMI]
It's happened before.

60
00:05:18,166 --> 00:05:21,375
In 1882, the Japanese army
used ship cannons

61
00:05:21,458 --> 00:05:23,833
in an attempt
to disperse locusts.

62
00:05:23,916 --> 00:05:25,333
Here's our story,

63
00:05:25,416 --> 00:05:27,875
in order to successfully
disperse a swarm of locusts

64
00:05:27,958 --> 00:05:30,291
moving up the eastern
coastline of Hokkaido,

65
00:05:30,375 --> 00:05:33,333
we requested direct aid
from Rear Admiral Koito,

66
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:36,541
the Commander of
the Ominato Guard District.

67
00:05:36,625 --> 00:05:37,833
Agreed.

68
00:05:37,916 --> 00:05:40,125
[TSURUMI]
During our return to Shari,

69
00:05:40,208 --> 00:05:42,875
a riot broke out
at Abashiri Prison.

70
00:05:42,958 --> 00:05:44,583
We happened to arrive
just in time

71
00:05:44,666 --> 00:05:46,166
to help put an end to it.

72
00:05:47,333 --> 00:05:49,416
I guarantee you,
no one from the mainland

73
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:51,333
is going to drag themselves
all the way out

74
00:05:51,416 --> 00:05:52,666
to the ends of the earth

75
00:05:52,750 --> 00:05:54,750
to investigate
either story for themselves.

76
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:56,333
Never have and never will.

77
00:05:56,416 --> 00:05:57,833
They're content
just to read reports

78
00:05:57,916 --> 00:05:59,875
and accept what we say.

79
00:05:59,958 --> 00:06:02,708
If even a single person from
the prison survives, though,

80
00:06:02,791 --> 00:06:03,916
we're screwed.

81
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,375
The entire thing comes apart.

82
00:06:07,916 --> 00:06:10,958
What makes you think
there'll be any survivors here?

83
00:06:11,041 --> 00:06:13,291
♪

84
00:06:15,958 --> 00:06:17,416
[snickers]

85
00:06:19,916 --> 00:06:21,250
[SOLDIER]
That's the actual army!

86
00:06:21,333 --> 00:06:22,625
We can't fight that.

87
00:06:22,708 --> 00:06:23,916
I'm surrendering.

88
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,708
But I heard they'll kill you
regardless.

89
00:06:25,791 --> 00:06:26,708
That's a lie.

90
00:06:26,791 --> 00:06:28,416
Warden Inudou spread that around

91
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:31,000
because he wanted us to think
we had no choice but to fight.

92
00:06:31,083 --> 00:06:32,500
-[gunshots]
-[BOTH gasp]

93
00:06:33,541 --> 00:06:34,458
[BOTH gasp]

94
00:06:34,541 --> 00:06:35,750
[gasps]
They're here!

95
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:37,833
♪

96
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,750
Please! Don't shoot!
I surrender!

97
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:42,833
[groans]

98
00:06:44,083 --> 00:06:45,583
[groans]

99
00:06:47,375 --> 00:06:48,333
Get to the cells!

100
00:06:48,416 --> 00:06:49,416
Hurry!

101
00:06:57,666 --> 00:06:59,916
Remember, they've come here
to kill us all.

102
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,458
If you don't fight back,

103
00:07:01,541 --> 00:07:04,625
then today will assuredly
be your last on this earth.

104
00:07:08,791 --> 00:07:09,833
[TANIGAKI]
Inkarmat!

105
00:07:10,833 --> 00:07:12,041
Inkarmat!

106
00:07:12,125 --> 00:07:13,500
Where are you?

107
00:07:13,583 --> 00:07:15,125
-[INKARMAT] Tanigaki Nispa.
-Huh?

108
00:07:16,125 --> 00:07:17,208
I'm coming.

109
00:07:20,291 --> 00:07:21,375
Are you all right?

110
00:07:21,458 --> 00:07:23,500
-[rumbling]
-[gasps]

111
00:07:23,583 --> 00:07:25,125
Please get out while you can.

112
00:07:26,833 --> 00:07:28,458
I'm not letting you die here.

113
00:07:29,916 --> 00:07:31,541
[grunting]

114
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,750
[screaming]

115
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:51,875
Move!

116
00:07:51,958 --> 00:07:53,583
-[INKARMAT breathing heavily]
-[TANIGAKI grunts]

117
00:08:01,916 --> 00:08:02,750
[gasps]

118
00:08:02,833 --> 00:08:04,333
[grunting]

119
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:08,375
Ushiyama.

120
00:08:08,458 --> 00:08:09,750
[grunts]

121
00:08:09,833 --> 00:08:11,416
Go on, get yourselves out.

122
00:08:12,583 --> 00:08:15,041
Now you, Ushiyama.
Just drop it and run.

123
00:08:15,125 --> 00:08:16,541
[grunting]

124
00:08:16,625 --> 00:08:19,875
You two kids had damn well
better be happy together.

125
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:21,375
[BOTH gasp]

126
00:08:21,458 --> 00:08:22,375
No, please.

127
00:08:22,458 --> 00:08:23,416
What are you doing?

128
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:24,708
[grunting]

129
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:27,666
[screams]

130
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:29,125
That was really heavy.

131
00:08:32,958 --> 00:08:34,833
Damn, got my jacket all dirty.

132
00:08:36,541 --> 00:08:38,166
♪

133
00:08:49,166 --> 00:08:52,083
Star shells were used
in the Russo-Japanese war.

134
00:08:52,166 --> 00:08:54,375
♪

135
00:09:09,875 --> 00:09:12,041
Sergeant Tsukishima, do it.

136
00:09:12,125 --> 00:09:13,166
Yes, sir.

137
00:09:17,708 --> 00:09:19,083
What'd they just throw at us?

138
00:09:24,791 --> 00:09:26,500
Charge, men,
I want 'em all dead!

139
00:09:26,583 --> 00:09:27,958
[SOLDIERS yelling]

140
00:09:35,666 --> 00:09:37,750
Shiraishi, what the hell?

141
00:09:37,833 --> 00:09:40,208
There's a narrow space
underneath each cell.

142
00:09:40,291 --> 00:09:42,750
It's what allows air in
and keeps it circulating.

143
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:44,250
[screaming]

144
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:46,000
Damn it, would you just shut up?

145
00:09:46,083 --> 00:09:48,250
Keep your nasty mouth shut.

146
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:50,458
[screaming]

147
00:09:50,541 --> 00:09:53,083
[BOTH screaming]

148
00:09:54,208 --> 00:09:56,375
[ASIRPA] Did you know
that Nopperabo was a fake?

149
00:09:58,750 --> 00:10:00,958
Wait, did Kadokura know, too?

150
00:10:01,041 --> 00:10:03,125
After we managed to escape,

151
00:10:03,208 --> 00:10:05,750
Warden Inudou secretly
removed the real Nopperabo

152
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:07,708
and switched him out
for a decoy.

153
00:10:07,791 --> 00:10:09,958
The thing is,
Kadokura spent seven years

154
00:10:10,041 --> 00:10:12,083
seeing Nopperabo
every single day.

155
00:10:12,166 --> 00:10:13,583
He simply isn't stupid enough

156
00:10:13,666 --> 00:10:15,250
to not have noticed
the difference.

157
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:17,958
Then he had to have known this
when he sent them in there.

158
00:10:20,583 --> 00:10:23,916
It's time for you
to come with us, Asirpa.

159
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,541
Or you'll miss your chance.

160
00:10:29,666 --> 00:10:31,375
♪

161
00:10:31,458 --> 00:10:32,458
[grunts]

162
00:10:33,708 --> 00:10:34,625
They're here.

163
00:10:34,708 --> 00:10:36,166
What are you doing? Run!

164
00:10:36,250 --> 00:10:37,416
[gunshot]

165
00:10:42,958 --> 00:10:44,541
Where is Nopperabo?

166
00:10:49,416 --> 00:10:50,375
[gasps]

167
00:10:51,916 --> 00:10:53,916
[KADOKURA]
Usami?

168
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,958
♪

169
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:58,208
Hmm.

170
00:11:02,958 --> 00:11:04,125
[chuckles]

171
00:11:04,208 --> 00:11:07,791
My, it's Immortal Sugimoto.

172
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:09,958
[ASIRPA]
I need to save him.

173
00:11:10,041 --> 00:11:12,750
I'm not leaving here
without Sugimoto.

174
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:15,458
If Nopperabo could
finally see his daughter,

175
00:11:15,541 --> 00:11:17,041
we feel that he might
then tell us

176
00:11:17,125 --> 00:11:18,750
where the gold is being hidden.

177
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:21,458
That is what we all want.

178
00:11:21,541 --> 00:11:23,000
Why we came here.

179
00:11:23,083 --> 00:11:24,708
You know Sugimoto.

180
00:11:24,791 --> 00:11:26,625
He would want to see
our goal achieved

181
00:11:26,708 --> 00:11:29,333
more than he would
care about himself.

182
00:11:29,416 --> 00:11:30,333
Get back!

183
00:11:30,416 --> 00:11:31,958
So we're clear.

184
00:11:32,041 --> 00:11:34,083
I haven't gotten the location
of the gold from him, yet.

185
00:11:40,416 --> 00:11:42,041
Where is my Aca now?

186
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:44,625
[TSURUMI]
As it happens,

187
00:11:44,708 --> 00:11:47,208
I've got 63
of my best men with me.

188
00:11:47,291 --> 00:11:49,041
Do you really think
you're going to be able

189
00:11:49,125 --> 00:11:50,916
to make some valiant escape?

190
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:53,125
Well, we're about to find out.

191
00:11:53,208 --> 00:11:55,000
All of you, throw down
your weapons, and then--

192
00:11:55,083 --> 00:11:56,000
[gasps]

193
00:11:56,083 --> 00:11:58,125
[TSURUMI]
Nikaidou!

194
00:11:58,208 --> 00:11:59,500
[grunts]

195
00:11:59,583 --> 00:12:00,833
Let me go!

196
00:12:00,916 --> 00:12:03,250
I'm gonna kill him.
That was the whole deal!

197
00:12:04,458 --> 00:12:05,833
Don't be an idiot!

198
00:12:05,916 --> 00:12:08,541
What happens if you end up
hitting Nopperabo?

199
00:12:08,625 --> 00:12:09,500
[gasps]

200
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:15,208
All of you, I want you
out of the building, now!

201
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:17,416
I'll blow his head off,
I swear I will!

202
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:18,583
You got that?

203
00:12:20,541 --> 00:12:22,375
Huh?

204
00:12:22,458 --> 00:12:24,333
[USAMI]
Chief Kadokura, it's you.

205
00:12:24,416 --> 00:12:25,708
[gasps]

206
00:12:25,791 --> 00:12:28,083
It's so great to see you again.

207
00:12:28,166 --> 00:12:29,250
[panting]

208
00:12:29,333 --> 00:12:31,208
Get that crazy mole
away from me!

209
00:12:31,291 --> 00:12:32,291
-[gunshot]
-[groans]

210
00:12:35,083 --> 00:12:37,333
My apologies, Chief Kadokura.

211
00:12:37,416 --> 00:12:38,875
I actually aimed for your neck.

212
00:12:39,916 --> 00:12:41,208
Hmm?

213
00:12:41,291 --> 00:12:43,833
[KADOKURA]
New kid, I just realized,

214
00:12:43,916 --> 00:12:47,500
I haven't explained how this
little guy works yet, have I?

215
00:12:47,583 --> 00:12:48,541
Hmm?

216
00:12:48,625 --> 00:12:49,625
Hmm.

217
00:12:50,625 --> 00:12:52,333
♪

218
00:12:52,416 --> 00:12:55,708
It's a device that unlocks
every cell at once.

219
00:12:55,791 --> 00:12:57,583
First used in Kabato Prison.

220
00:13:01,875 --> 00:13:02,916
[gasps]

221
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:03,916
[laughs]

222
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,250
You feeling ready to face down

223
00:13:05,333 --> 00:13:08,375
700 deadly criminals
with cabin fever?

224
00:13:11,083 --> 00:13:11,958
Huh?

225
00:13:13,083 --> 00:13:15,541
♪

226
00:13:15,625 --> 00:13:17,083
[PRISONERS yelling]

227
00:13:19,583 --> 00:13:20,583
[gasps]

228
00:13:31,458 --> 00:13:32,666
Bayonets!

229
00:13:34,541 --> 00:13:36,208
[yelling]

230
00:13:36,291 --> 00:13:39,166
I want you to exterminate
every last one.

231
00:13:43,041 --> 00:13:44,416
[yelling]

232
00:13:46,083 --> 00:13:48,541
[gunshots]

233
00:13:57,208 --> 00:13:58,791
[grunts]
Here I come!

234
00:13:58,875 --> 00:13:59,875
[gasps]

235
00:14:04,791 --> 00:14:06,250
Come out, wherever you are.

236
00:14:09,708 --> 00:14:10,833
That old bastard.

237
00:14:10,916 --> 00:14:12,458
Hijikata must've
set this whole thing up.

238
00:14:12,541 --> 00:14:14,791
If Toni Anji
was working with him,

239
00:14:14,875 --> 00:14:16,416
he might be with Asirpa now.

240
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:18,083
Hijikata's using us.

241
00:14:18,166 --> 00:14:19,875
Damn schemer.

242
00:14:19,958 --> 00:14:22,250
He sent us into the cell block
with the fake Nopperabo

243
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:24,041
because he knew
the commotion would cause

244
00:14:24,125 --> 00:14:26,375
Inudou to panic
and bolt for the place

245
00:14:26,458 --> 00:14:29,416
where the real Nopperabo
was being kept.

246
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:30,833
It's clear now.

247
00:14:30,916 --> 00:14:32,958
That was the plan
from the very beginning.

248
00:14:34,416 --> 00:14:36,166
[SUGIMOTO]
So while Kadokura and the guards

249
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:37,625
kept us pinned down here,

250
00:14:37,708 --> 00:14:39,583
he would bring Asirpa
to meet her father,

251
00:14:39,666 --> 00:14:41,916
learn the location of the gold
and escape.

252
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,583
[inaudible]

253
00:14:43,666 --> 00:14:47,500
And as a bonus, he's using this
to separate me and Asirpa.

254
00:14:48,541 --> 00:14:51,458
He knows
I'll get in his way, eventually.

255
00:14:51,541 --> 00:14:53,333
♪

256
00:14:53,416 --> 00:14:54,541
[grunting]

257
00:15:00,125 --> 00:15:01,291
Easy.

258
00:15:01,375 --> 00:15:03,708
You just have to
dislocate both shoulders.

259
00:15:03,791 --> 00:15:04,875
[SUGIMOTO]
Are you kidding?

260
00:15:04,958 --> 00:15:06,250
Just great.

261
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:08,000
There's gotta be another way out
besides this.

262
00:15:08,083 --> 00:15:10,583
I'll find something
I can use to break the wall.

263
00:15:10,666 --> 00:15:12,625
[SUGIMOTO]
No. I'll get out on my own.

264
00:15:12,708 --> 00:15:14,208
Go look for Asirpa.

265
00:15:14,291 --> 00:15:17,416
Once you've got her, go wait
for me at the main gate.

266
00:15:18,583 --> 00:15:21,041
You better take care of her,
you hear me?

267
00:15:35,625 --> 00:15:38,666
There. It's the chapel,
just like I thought.

268
00:15:39,750 --> 00:15:42,375
Inudou comes here
every day to practice,

269
00:15:42,458 --> 00:15:45,666
so I already had
my suspicions about it.

270
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:48,125
But no matter how many times
Kadokura searched the place,

271
00:15:48,208 --> 00:15:50,916
he couldn't find
any hidden rooms.

272
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:53,000
You're saying
Aca is here, right?

273
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:54,833
[HIJIKATA] All we have to do
is catch Inudou

274
00:15:54,916 --> 00:15:56,958
when he tries
to move Nopperabo.

275
00:16:00,708 --> 00:16:02,625
[groaning]

276
00:16:02,708 --> 00:16:04,375
What's wrong?

277
00:16:04,458 --> 00:16:05,625
[TONI]
Let's get into the building.

278
00:16:05,708 --> 00:16:06,958
My eardrums hurt.

279
00:16:07,041 --> 00:16:08,041
Hmm.

280
00:16:08,125 --> 00:16:10,125
Where'd she go?

281
00:16:10,208 --> 00:16:11,041
Huh?

282
00:16:11,125 --> 00:16:12,500
[ASIRPA panting]

283
00:16:12,583 --> 00:16:15,000
[HIJIKATA] So she's headed back
to Sugimoto, huh?

284
00:16:15,083 --> 00:16:17,166
She vanished the second
she learned the truth

285
00:16:17,250 --> 00:16:19,500
about where
Nopperabo really was.

286
00:16:19,583 --> 00:16:22,333
I'll say this,
that little girl's a tough one.

287
00:16:22,416 --> 00:16:24,291
-Do we bring her back?
-Not now.

288
00:16:24,375 --> 00:16:27,250
Our priority has to be
intercepting Inudou.

289
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:29,500
I guess I'll have to
resort to using these

290
00:16:29,583 --> 00:16:30,958
in order to make him believe.

291
00:16:33,166 --> 00:16:34,416
[panting]

292
00:16:36,333 --> 00:16:37,583
[gasps]

293
00:16:37,666 --> 00:16:38,791
Quiet.

294
00:16:38,875 --> 00:16:40,541
[SOLDIER]
Hurry! Come on.

295
00:16:40,625 --> 00:16:41,583
[sighs]

296
00:16:43,041 --> 00:16:44,666
[ASIRPA]
Shiraishi.

297
00:16:44,750 --> 00:16:45,833
Oh, there you are.

298
00:16:45,916 --> 00:16:47,541
Where's Sugimoto?

299
00:16:47,625 --> 00:16:49,250
[SHIRAISHI] He's still trapped
beneath the floors of the cells.

300
00:16:49,333 --> 00:16:51,750
The air duct was so small
that only I could get out.

301
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:53,125
Hang on, wait.

302
00:16:53,208 --> 00:16:54,500
You can't go after him.

303
00:16:54,583 --> 00:16:55,958
There are too many soldiers.

304
00:16:56,041 --> 00:16:57,333
But...

305
00:16:57,416 --> 00:17:00,708
Asirpa, will you trust me
to go save Sugimoto?

306
00:17:00,791 --> 00:17:03,583
Yes, and once you do, you should
take him to the chapel.

307
00:17:03,666 --> 00:17:06,416
According to Hijikata,
that's where Nopperabo is kept.

308
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,750
But we really
can't do that, either.

309
00:17:08,833 --> 00:17:10,291
I'm sorry.

310
00:17:10,375 --> 00:17:12,125
Sugimoto instructed me
to take you to the main gate.

311
00:17:12,208 --> 00:17:13,541
No.

312
00:17:13,625 --> 00:17:15,708
I have to meet Aca
and see if it's really him.

313
00:17:15,791 --> 00:17:18,708
No, listen, you can't go back
to Hijikata, you hear me?

314
00:17:18,791 --> 00:17:20,333
For your own good.

315
00:17:20,416 --> 00:17:22,708
We think he's been trying to
separate you from Sugimoto.

316
00:17:22,791 --> 00:17:23,875
[gasps]

317
00:17:23,958 --> 00:17:25,250
It won't work.

318
00:17:25,333 --> 00:17:28,541
Once I save Sugimoto,
I'll go to the chapel.

319
00:17:28,625 --> 00:17:31,208
As for Nopperabo, we'll get him
to the main gate.

320
00:17:31,291 --> 00:17:32,916
[ASIRPA]
Wait.

321
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,750
Give it to Sugimoto.

322
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:36,208
[PRISONERS yelling]

323
00:17:36,291 --> 00:17:38,125
♪

324
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:49,791
[grunting]

325
00:17:49,875 --> 00:17:52,333
How the hell do you dislocate
your shoulders, anyway?

326
00:17:52,416 --> 00:17:54,541
-[KIRORANKE] Sugimoto.
-[SUGIMOTO] Kiroranke.

327
00:17:55,791 --> 00:17:56,916
Are you kidding me?

328
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,750
There's no way out of that.

329
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:00,125
What you doin'?

330
00:18:00,208 --> 00:18:01,916
Gonna jam
a few of these grenades,

331
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,583
between the wall and the dirt.

332
00:18:03,666 --> 00:18:04,666
[gasps]

333
00:18:05,958 --> 00:18:07,375
[screams]

334
00:18:07,458 --> 00:18:08,541
[KIRORANKE]
Might wanna back up!

335
00:18:09,583 --> 00:18:10,583
Wait, just a sec!

336
00:18:13,125 --> 00:18:14,125
Huh?

337
00:18:14,208 --> 00:18:15,375
Did he fart?

338
00:18:18,791 --> 00:18:19,958
[coughing]

339
00:18:21,458 --> 00:18:22,791
The chapel, huh?

340
00:18:22,875 --> 00:18:24,458
Asirpa said you should
show this to Nopperabo.

341
00:18:24,541 --> 00:18:26,125
[sighs]

342
00:18:26,208 --> 00:18:29,625
Yes, it's Asirpa's makiri.

343
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:31,000
The one her father made.

344
00:18:32,291 --> 00:18:35,833
Go wait at the main gate,
she's alone with Shiraishi.

345
00:18:36,833 --> 00:18:39,166
I'll make sure
Nopperabo gets there.

346
00:18:39,250 --> 00:18:42,291
Give her my promise,
that she'll see him very soon.

347
00:18:42,375 --> 00:18:43,458
Will do.

348
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:47,166
♪

349
00:19:03,291 --> 00:19:04,250
[grunts]

350
00:19:05,458 --> 00:19:06,833
[grunting]

351
00:19:09,291 --> 00:19:10,333
[gasps]

352
00:19:16,583 --> 00:19:19,583
I think I keep hearing
something from below.

353
00:19:19,666 --> 00:19:22,125
So there's a basement
after all, then.

354
00:19:22,208 --> 00:19:24,208
♪

355
00:19:30,875 --> 00:19:32,375
[grunts]

356
00:19:32,458 --> 00:19:33,416
Get out.

357
00:19:34,833 --> 00:19:38,041
I will gladly put out
both of Inudou's beady eyes.

358
00:19:45,958 --> 00:19:47,625
[groans]

359
00:19:47,708 --> 00:19:49,583
♪

360
00:19:51,916 --> 00:19:52,791
Huh!

361
00:20:04,250 --> 00:20:05,250
Hmm.

362
00:20:11,541 --> 00:20:12,458
[grunts]

363
00:20:13,958 --> 00:20:14,833
[grunts]

364
00:20:20,333 --> 00:20:22,625
Looks like it's till
death do us part, old man.

365
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:29,208
[screaming]

366
00:20:30,416 --> 00:20:32,583
[grunting]

367
00:20:32,666 --> 00:20:33,916
[groans]

368
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:35,041
[grunts]

369
00:20:37,916 --> 00:20:39,250
[grunting]

370
00:20:43,875 --> 00:20:44,791
[SUGIMOTO]
What?

371
00:20:47,958 --> 00:20:49,333
[groaning]

372
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:54,500
Yohei, Sugimoto will be
joining you soon!

373
00:20:54,583 --> 00:20:55,875
[grunting]

374
00:21:04,583 --> 00:21:07,416
Hey, look.
Somebody's on the ground.

375
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:08,833
It's Nikaidou.

376
00:21:08,916 --> 00:21:10,625
Is he alive?

377
00:21:10,708 --> 00:21:12,500
♪

378
00:21:14,708 --> 00:21:19,625
All right, Nopperabo,
let's get you to Asirpa.

379
00:21:19,708 --> 00:21:21,125
She's waiting for you.

380
00:21:21,208 --> 00:21:22,333
[SHIRAISHI]
Hmm.

381
00:21:23,458 --> 00:21:26,041
Wait. Someone's coming.

382
00:21:26,125 --> 00:21:27,291
Oh, look who it is.

383
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:34,041
Good to see ya.

384
00:21:34,125 --> 00:21:35,625
Where's Sugimoto?

385
00:21:35,708 --> 00:21:38,083
I was able to break him
out of the prison,

386
00:21:38,166 --> 00:21:40,333
but then he went
to the chapel alone.

387
00:21:40,416 --> 00:21:43,083
He sends his promise
that you'll meet Nopperabo soon.

388
00:21:45,166 --> 00:21:48,333
Hijikata and Inudou are
both there at the chapel, too.

389
00:21:48,416 --> 00:21:49,541
Let's go.

390
00:21:50,625 --> 00:21:52,208
Nope, sorry,
you're staying here.

391
00:21:52,291 --> 00:21:53,333
But...

392
00:21:54,750 --> 00:21:56,041
Where are you going?

393
00:21:57,041 --> 00:21:59,458
Maybe I can see
what's going on from up here.

394
00:22:07,958 --> 00:22:09,041
[groaning]

395
00:22:29,833 --> 00:22:30,958
[gasps]

396
00:22:32,416 --> 00:22:33,458
[SUGIMOTO]
Blue eyes.

397
00:24:06,875 --> 00:24:09,208
[NARRATOR]
Next time, "Call Out."

